virex firm book  editions published in  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide reverse osmosis demineralization of acid mine drainage by inc rex chainbelt book  editions published in  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide a twophase study involving both laboratory and field investigations has demonstrated the feasibility of using reverse osmosis to provide potable water from acid mine drainage the laboratory investigations involved the determination of methods for controlling iron fouling and the selection of a process flow sheet during the field test the process developed in phase i was used to treat acid mine drainage from an underground abandoned anthracite coal mine treatment prior to reverse osmosis consisted of filtration  microns followed by ultraviolet light disinfection brine from the ro unit was treated by neutralization oxidation and settling results obtained indicated that membrane fouling due to iron was satisfactorily controlled but calcium sulfate fouling limited the recovery of product water to about  product water was of potable quality in all respects except for iron manganese and ph calcium sulfate precipitate on the ro membrane was successfully removed using a solution of ammoniated citric acid at ph  screeningflotation treatment of combined sewer overflows by inc rex chainbelt book  editions published in  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide the report documents a study to develop a treatment system for combined sewer overflows the processes of chemical oxidation screening dissolvedair flotation and disinfection were evaluated in the laboratory a  mgd demonstration system was designed installed and evaluated suspended solids and volatile suspended solids removal in the range of  were consistently obtained at influent concentrations of  to  mgl bod and cod removals were slightly lower at  to  for influent concentrations of  to  mgl addition of chemical flocculents ferric chloride and a cationic polyelectrolyte was necessary to obtain these removals without the use of chemical flocculents removal of bod cod suspended solids and volatile suspended solids were all in the range of  the screening flotation system provided sufficient detention time difference  minutes for adequate disinfection with hypochlorite salts cost estimates are presented amenability of reverse osmosis concentrate to activated sludge treatment by mahendra k gupta book  editions published in  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide pilot scale tubular and spiral wound reverse osmosis ro units were used to establish the feasibility of renovating municipal sewage results indicated that prior treatment with ferric chloride and alum will be necessary even when using the tubular ro system ro produced an approximate  mg tds of inorganic ions in the effluent but an estimated  to  of the soluble organic material permeated the membranes at high feed water recoveries approximately  of the organic material passing the membrane was ethanol but other organics may pass through the membranes from other sewages  water recovery rates with no precipitation problems in the ro concentrate were achieved but ro product waters would require further treatment for organic removal prior to discharge the feasibility of biodegrading ro concentrates was also established development of a mobile treatment system for handling spilled hazardous materials by mahendra k gupta book  edition published in  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide constituents of highway runoff book  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide screeningflotation treatment of combined sewer overflows book  editions published in  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide constituents of highway runoff  vol iv characteristics of runoff from operating highways  final report book  edition published in  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide co